---
description: Component strategy (duplication-first, reference-first)
globs: src/components/**/*.tsx
alwaysApply: false
---

# Component Strategy (Early Stage)

- Build reusable components only.
- Keep components simple and readable.
- Prefer duplication over premature abstraction.
- Do not generalize components too early.
- Focus on matching the UI reference first (layout/structure); pixel-perfect is allowed.
- Refactor later once the structure is validated.
- For components with variants, keep one clear props contract and render from props, not ad-hoc style branches.
- Reuse a shared variant naming scheme across components:
  - `size`: `small | medium | large`
  - booleans like `flush`, `expanded`
  - interaction state keys like `default | hover | pressed | focused` when needed by design review/demo.

# Styling Inside Components

- Use Tailwind for layout/spacing/border/radius/shadow.
- Use palette utilities from `colors.css` (e.g. `bg-gray-100`, `text-gray-900`) — no hex/rgb in class strings beyond what Tailwind generates from `@theme`.
- **Fonts:** rely on `body` for UI (inherit); use `font-content` only for long Arabic reading content per `typography.mdc`.
- **Class lists:** build every `className` with `twMerge` from `tailwind-merge`. Do not add a local `cx` / `classNames` helper that only joins strings — `twMerge` resolves conflicting Tailwind utilities and accepts conditional args (`false` / `undefined` are ignored).
- Merge consumer `className` with defaults via `twMerge(defaults, className)` so overrides win for conflicting utilities.
